1
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,000
"Lost To You"

2
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,700
(Episode 6)

3
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:00,499
We tentatively drew closer,

4
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:04,599
only to run into a figure
who shouldn't be there.

5
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:06,999
Jealousy is a silent tsunami,

6
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,500
drowning all our unspoken understanding.

7
00:01:18,458 --> 00:01:19,458
Are you okay?

8
00:01:28,791 --> 00:01:29,791
I'm sorry.

9
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:31,530
I didn't know you couldn't swim.

10
00:01:33,375 --> 00:01:34,375
You lied to me.

11
00:01:35,916 --> 00:01:37,596
I didn't realize you were afraid of water.

12
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:39,601
I thought you just didn't like it much.

13
00:01:40,916 --> 00:01:41,916
Why did you jump?

14
00:01:44,833 --> 00:01:45,833
I just wanted to know...

15
00:01:47,916 --> 00:01:49,036
if you really meant it...

16
00:01:49,708 --> 00:01:50,948
when you said you'd save me.

17
00:01:52,250 --> 00:01:53,250
Now you know.

18
00:01:58,041 --> 00:01:59,041
I know.

19
00:02:00,541 --> 00:02:01,941
Even though you're afraid of water,

20
00:02:03,750 --> 00:02:05,041
you'd still jump in to save me.

21
00:02:10,916 --> 00:02:14,870
Why... are you afraid of water?

22
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:26,250
Because of my dad.

23
00:02:29,083 --> 00:02:30,333
He died at sea.

24
00:02:34,041 --> 00:02:35,041
The year I was born,

25
00:02:36,666 --> 00:02:38,375
an old fortune teller came to town.

26
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:40,973
He said I was born under an unlucky star.

27
00:02:43,125 --> 00:02:44,445
But my dad refused to believe it.

28
00:02:46,333 --> 00:02:47,666
He said on the day I was born,

29
00:02:49,166 --> 00:02:51,125
the sky was blue and the sea was calm.

30
00:02:53,083 --> 00:02:54,958
I must have been a gift
sent to him from the heavens.

31
00:02:57,666 --> 00:02:59,250
That's why he named me Xu Yuan
[TN: "Make a wish" in mandarin]]

32
00:03:02,125 --> 00:03:03,208
His wish was...

33
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:07,011
for me to live a safe and peaceful life.

34
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:13,416
Then, when I was ten,

35
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:16,875
he took me out on the boat.

36
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:21,733
I accidentally fell into the water.

37
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:25,833
To save me,

38
00:03:26,416 --> 00:03:28,136
he used all his strength to push me ashore.

39
00:03:31,125 --> 00:03:32,500
But he never made it back up.

40
00:03:35,625 --> 00:03:36,625
After that,

41
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:39,750
everyone in town said...

42
00:03:42,875 --> 00:03:44,791
the curse of the Jinx had come true.

43
00:03:48,125 --> 00:03:49,125
Ever since then,

44
00:03:51,458 --> 00:03:52,541
I've been afraid of water.

45
00:03:55,208 --> 00:03:56,333
That wasn't your fault.

46
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,500
It was never your fault.

47
00:04:11,041 --> 00:04:15,118
I'll tell you one of... my secrets.

48
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:18,973
Actually, I'm just like my older brother.

49
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,750
I'm also the "monster" my dad talks about.

50
00:04:26,125 --> 00:04:27,125
I like men.

51
00:04:31,875 --> 00:04:32,875
I'm scared...

52
00:04:34,166 --> 00:04:35,406
of becoming like my brother.

53
00:04:36,083 --> 00:04:38,541
So I desperately tried to
convince myself to be normal.

54
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:43,416
But I know...

55
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:47,250
how I really feel.

56
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:56,500
This is something...

57
00:04:58,333 --> 00:04:59,833
I've never told anyone before.

58
00:05:05,583 --> 00:05:06,583
Now you know.

59
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:14,625
I'm trading my secret...

60
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:17,083
for your secret.

61
00:05:18,958 --> 00:05:19,958
Now we're even.

62
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:32,333
Thank you.

63
00:05:35,875 --> 00:05:36,875
For what?

64
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:41,958
Thank you for telling me...

65
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:49,313
that the sea swallows people up,

66
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:51,733
and that what happened to my dad...

67
00:05:53,208 --> 00:05:54,208
was never your fault.

68
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:00,791
Liking men...

69
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:04,000
is not your fault either.

70
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,980
So let's both stop blaming ourselves.

71
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,000
I'll be with you.

72
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:58,500
Do you mind?

73
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:01,333
What?

74
00:07:06,625 --> 00:07:07,905
Yesterday on the fishing boat...

75
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:10,541
the secret I told you.

76
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:13,000
Do you think it's weird?

77
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:21,541
No.

78
00:07:22,625 --> 00:07:23,625
We're good friends.

79
00:07:24,166 --> 00:07:25,166
Why would I mind?

80
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,580
Pass it here, pass it here!

81
00:08:34,041 --> 00:08:34,675
Here!

82
00:08:34,791 --> 00:08:35,608
Zhan Wang!

83
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:40,833
Come on, come on!

84
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:43,750
Thanks.

85
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:31,333
One more day.

86
00:09:40,146 --> 00:09:43,639
[An unbelievably sad string of unanswered texts
to his dad, ending with "Dad, It's my birthday"]

87
00:10:01,353 --> 00:10:05,086
[He's considering deleting his
WeChat conversation with his dad]

88
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:45,666
What are you doing here?

89
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:48,946
There's a problem I can't solve,

90
00:10:49,375 --> 00:10:50,375
so I came to ask you.

91
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:51,750
Is that not okay?

92
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:53,000
No problem.

93
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:57,750
The power must be out.

94
00:10:58,500 --> 00:10:59,041
I'll go check.

95
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:00,125
It's okay.

96
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:01,958
I have this.

97
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:08,333
This is for you.

98
00:11:08,541 --> 00:11:10,000
Next time the power goes out,

99
00:11:10,583 --> 00:11:11,663
you can use this for light.

100
00:11:14,166 --> 00:11:15,333
I have something to give to you too.

101
00:11:26,125 --> 00:11:27,125
Wang-wang.

102
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:28,708
Happy birthday.

103
00:11:32,291 --> 00:11:33,291
How did you know...

104
00:11:34,166 --> 00:11:35,166
it was my birthday?

105
00:11:36,041 --> 00:11:37,041
I...

106
00:11:37,611 --> 00:11:38,611
of course I knew.

107
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,000
Yuan.

108
00:11:51,666 --> 00:11:52,666
Thank you.

109
00:13:13,386 --> 00:13:18,143
["His fingers ran through his partner's sweaty
hair, the moment their lips drew close..."]

110
00:13:18,708 --> 00:13:19,708
Bro.

111
00:13:21,875 --> 00:13:23,083
You're reading this?

112
00:13:24,583 --> 00:13:25,583
Xu Nuo.

113
00:13:26,208 --> 00:13:28,248
You're the one who put
this on my bookshelf, right?

114
00:13:29,541 --> 00:13:31,750
Well, Mom doesn't go through your stuff.

115
00:13:32,416 --> 00:13:33,083
So? What do you think?

116
00:13:33,416 --> 00:13:34,458
Isn't it super intense?

117
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:36,166
Let me tell you,

118
00:13:39,625 --> 00:13:40,958
this pool scene...

119
00:13:41,166 --> 00:13:43,375
I dog-eared the page specifically.

120
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:45,291
It's so perfect for you and Zhan Wang!

121
00:13:45,958 --> 00:13:46,958
Stop talking nonsense.

122
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:50,750
Oh, stop pretending.

123
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:52,208
I can totally see it.

124
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:55,083
You and Zhan Wang have
been inseparable lately.

125
00:13:55,666 --> 00:13:57,625
The way he looks at you...

126
00:14:00,166 --> 00:14:01,166
So...

127
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,791
you guys should go on a proper date.

128
00:14:04,125 --> 00:14:05,791
Find a thrilling environment.

129
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:07,375
Get your hearts racing.

130
00:14:07,750 --> 00:14:09,666
It's a catalyst for love.

131
00:14:10,625 --> 00:14:11,785
If you keep talking nonsense,

132
00:14:12,875 --> 00:14:13,875
I'll tell Mom...

133
00:14:14,041 --> 00:14:15,875
that you read novels in class.

134
00:14:16,625 --> 00:14:18,225
And have her cancel your acting classes.

135
00:14:21,083 --> 00:14:22,083
Okay, okay.

136
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:23,458
I'll stop.

137
00:14:25,875 --> 00:14:26,875
But, bro...

138
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:29,958
if you really like Zhan Wang,

139
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:31,333
you should be brave.

140
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:32,958
I can tell.

141
00:14:33,416 --> 00:14:35,416
Zhan Wang is so good to you.

142
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,500
And you're good to him too.

143
00:14:40,291 --> 00:14:41,291
Xu Yuan.

144
00:14:47,416 --> 00:14:47,916
What is it?

145
00:14:48,041 --> 00:14:49,041
Get on.

146
00:14:49,083 --> 00:14:49,541
Where are we going?

147
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:51,273
Don't worry about that. Just get in.

148
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:55,750
Let's go.

149
00:15:09,625 --> 00:15:11,225
What are we doing here so late at night?

150
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,958
Didn't you say you wanted
to learn how to swim?

151
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:18,331
Where did you get the keys?

152
00:15:18,791 --> 00:15:20,708
I borrowed it from the equipment room.

153
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:22,083
You stole it, didn't you?

154
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:24,250
Borrowed, borrowed, borrowed.

155
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:26,250
Come on.

156
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:39,958
Xu Yuan.

157
00:15:41,875 --> 00:15:42,875
Xu Yuan.

158
00:15:46,708 --> 00:15:47,708
I don't want to go in.

159
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:48,875
Why not?

160
00:15:49,166 --> 00:15:50,666
Didn't you say you wanted to learn?

161
00:15:51,375 --> 00:15:52,375
I changed my mind.

162
00:15:54,791 --> 00:15:55,791
Is it because of...

163
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:57,868
what happened to your dad?

164
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:03,833
Xu Yuan.

165
00:16:04,708 --> 00:16:06,508
You can't be afraid of
water your whole life.

166
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,541
Running away won't solve anything.

167
00:16:08,666 --> 00:16:09,666
I don't need to solve it.

168
00:16:10,625 --> 00:16:11,825
I just won't get in the water.

169
00:16:11,916 --> 00:16:13,125
What if that person was me?

170
00:16:14,166 --> 00:16:15,286
What if I fell in the water?

171
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:17,125
Would you just watch?

172
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:18,375
Like with your dad?

173
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:31,416
Trust me.

174
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:33,291
Just this once.

175
00:16:55,166 --> 00:16:56,166
Come on down.

176
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:01,083
Come on down.

177
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,000
Give me your hand.

178
00:17:44,416 --> 00:17:46,250
You smell like mints.

179
00:17:47,250 --> 00:17:48,570
I can smell it even in the water.

180
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:52,333
Okay, how about this?

181
00:17:52,791 --> 00:17:54,351
I'll teach you how to hold your breath.

182
00:17:54,958 --> 00:17:55,958
Okay.

183
00:18:01,458 --> 00:18:02,458
How was that?

184
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:04,625
Breathe. Relax.

185
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:07,708
When the water reaches
your chin, exhale slowly.

186
00:18:08,291 --> 00:18:09,291
I'll show you first.

187
00:18:09,708 --> 00:18:10,708
Okay.

188
00:18:26,541 --> 00:18:27,541
See?

189
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,250
Got it?

190
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:32,286
Why don't you do it with me?

191
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,000
Trust me.

192
00:18:34,041 --> 00:18:35,041
Let's try it together.

193
00:18:36,291 --> 00:18:37,916
I'll count to three.
We'll go down together.

194
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:39,333
Okay.

195
00:18:39,583 --> 00:18:40,583
One.

196
00:18:40,625 --> 00:18:41,125
Two.

197
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:42,625
Three.

198
00:18:59,291 --> 00:19:00,291
You okay?

199
00:19:00,583 --> 00:19:01,823
Let's hold it longer this time.

200
00:19:02,541 --> 00:19:03,916
If you can't, just tap me.

201
00:19:04,041 --> 00:19:04,541
Okay.

202
00:19:04,791 --> 00:19:05,208
You can do it.

203
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:06,750
Three.

204
00:19:07,125 --> 00:19:08,125
Two.

205
00:19:08,583 --> 00:19:09,583
One.

206
00:19:27,041 --> 00:19:28,041
Who's there?

207
00:19:29,916 --> 00:19:31,083
The pool is closed at night.

208
00:19:32,666 --> 00:19:33,666
Come out.

209
00:19:34,416 --> 00:19:35,456
I know someone's in there.

210
00:19:37,083 --> 00:19:38,708
Sneaking in for a swim, are we?

211
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:30,458
Zhan Wang. Xu Yuan.

212
00:20:31,625 --> 00:20:32,625
Get out of there, now!

213
00:20:32,791 --> 00:20:33,791
Well, well. You two.

214
00:20:36,541 --> 00:20:37,625
Getting bold, aren't you?

215
00:20:38,583 --> 00:20:39,291
Stealing the key.

216
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:40,583
Sneaking into the pool.

217
00:20:40,791 --> 00:20:42,511
Do you have any idea how dangerous this is?

218
00:20:42,708 --> 00:20:43,948
What if something had happened?

219
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:45,000
I'm sorry, teacher.

220
00:20:45,041 --> 00:20:46,041
We were wrong.

221
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:48,625
T-Teacher, I'm sorry.

222
00:20:49,041 --> 00:20:50,521
Is just saying sorry going to cut it?

223
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,124
Today, you dare to steal a
key and sneak into the pool.

224
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,184
Tomorrow, will you be
breaking into the science lab?

225
00:20:55,208 --> 00:20:57,328
And the day after that,
you'll be completely lawless?

226
00:20:57,666 --> 00:20:59,106
No respect for rules. No discipline.

227
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:01,500
When I was underwater just now,

228
00:21:01,708 --> 00:21:02,708
I was saving you.

229
00:21:03,166 --> 00:21:04,166
Don't get the wrong idea.

230
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:06,291
School property is public property.

231
00:21:06,708 --> 00:21:07,541
Does that key belong to you?

232
00:21:07,625 --> 00:21:08,625
You don't believe me?

233
00:21:08,958 --> 00:21:09,625
If you don't believe me,

234
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:10,833
next time I'll show you

235
00:21:10,958 --> 00:21:12,118
the underwater rescue manual.

236
00:21:12,791 --> 00:21:13,871
Also, your lung capacity...

237
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:15,200
You really need to work on it.

238
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:16,953
Do you know how to train it?

239
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:19,583
Do you?

240
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:21,000
If you don't know,

241
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:22,833
I'll teach you next time.

242
00:21:29,958 --> 00:21:31,500
Did you hear a word I said?

243
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:33,583
Yes, sir.

244
00:21:34,208 --> 00:21:34,708
Loud and clear.

245
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:35,500
Get back to your dorms.

246
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:36,665
And await your punishment.

247
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:38,000
Go.

248
00:21:38,875 --> 00:21:39,875
Goodbye, teacher.

249
00:21:40,958 --> 00:21:41,958
Beat it.

250
00:21:49,375 --> 00:21:50,375
Are you asleep?

251
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:57,833
Not yet.

252
00:21:58,125 --> 00:21:59,125
What's up?

253
00:22:03,958 --> 00:22:05,934
Tomorrow, you can help
me with my boxing practice.

254
00:22:05,958 --> 00:22:07,434
And I'll help you with your lung capacity.

255
00:22:07,458 --> 00:22:08,458
Deal?

256
00:22:10,541 --> 00:22:11,541
Deal.

257
00:22:12,208 --> 00:22:12,916
It's a deal then.

258
00:22:13,041 --> 00:22:14,375
Get some sleep. Good night.

259
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:16,375
Good night.

260
00:22:57,916 --> 00:22:59,708
You smell like mints.

261
00:23:00,666 --> 00:23:02,066
I could even smell it in the water.

262
00:23:43,333 --> 00:23:45,583
Let's check, Teacher Xu.

263
00:23:51,625 --> 00:23:52,625
Class.

264
00:23:52,791 --> 00:23:54,458
I'd like to introduce a new student.

265
00:23:55,125 --> 00:23:56,791
Her name is Lin Xia.

266
00:23:57,125 --> 00:23:58,708
She's an art student from Jingzhou.

267
00:23:58,916 --> 00:24:00,276
She's here in Hong Town to sketch.

268
00:24:00,333 --> 00:24:01,809
She'll be studying with us for a while.

269
00:24:01,833 --> 00:24:03,033
Let's give her a warm welcome.

270
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,000
Find a seat for yourself.

271
00:24:21,500 --> 00:24:22,500
Zhan Wang.

272
00:24:22,708 --> 00:24:23,708
Long time no see.

273
00:24:25,666 --> 00:24:26,666
What are you doing here?

274
00:24:27,708 --> 00:24:29,041
Uncle was worried about you.

275
00:24:29,416 --> 00:24:30,791
So he had me come check on you.

276
00:24:32,083 --> 00:24:33,523
And to check on your second brother.

277
00:24:33,708 --> 00:24:34,708
I knew it.

278
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:36,040
That's all he cares about.

279
00:24:36,958 --> 00:24:38,318
He wants you to keep an eye on me.

280
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:40,800
He's afraid I'll get too
close to my brother.

281
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,000
Hi.

282
00:24:47,125 --> 00:24:48,125
I'm Lin Xia.

283
00:24:48,458 --> 00:24:50,458
You must be Zhan Wang's friend.

284
00:24:56,458 --> 00:24:58,083
It seems you two are pretty close.

285
00:24:59,625 --> 00:25:00,708
Zhan Wang is stubborn.

286
00:25:01,250 --> 00:25:02,410
He doesn't have many friends.

287
00:25:02,958 --> 00:25:04,416
For you to be his friend...

288
00:25:05,041 --> 00:25:06,083
is quite impressive.

289
00:25:09,375 --> 00:25:10,625
I'm Zhan Wang's fiancée.

290
00:25:11,375 --> 00:25:12,375
Lin Xia.

291
00:25:12,791 --> 00:25:14,231
What nonsense are you talking about?

292
00:25:14,833 --> 00:25:15,958
What nonsense?

293
00:25:16,625 --> 00:25:18,000
Didn't our families agree on it?

294
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,000
Or...

295
00:25:20,958 --> 00:25:21,541
am I wrong?

296
00:25:21,958 --> 00:25:22,958
Zhan Wang.

297
00:25:23,958 --> 00:25:25,059
It was arranged by our families.

298
00:25:25,083 --> 00:25:26,083
It doesn't mean anything.

299
00:25:28,791 --> 00:25:29,911
What are you all looking at?

300
00:25:31,375 --> 00:25:32,535
Stop it. Don't talk nonsense.

301
00:25:56,208 --> 00:25:57,267
That girl who just went upstairs,

302
00:25:57,291 --> 00:25:58,875
she's the new transfer student.

303
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:01,125
I saw her by the field earlier.

304
00:26:01,708 --> 00:26:02,833
White dress, long hair.

305
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:03,625
Carrying a sketchpad.

306
00:26:03,875 --> 00:26:05,333
She looked like a fairy.

307
00:26:06,041 --> 00:26:07,642
I heard she's an art student from Jingzhou.

308
00:26:07,666 --> 00:26:09,059
And that she's won an
international painting award.

309
00:26:09,083 --> 00:26:10,416
No wonder she's so elegant.

310
00:26:10,625 --> 00:26:11,976
Compared to the girls at our school,

311
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,080
she's completely different.

312
00:26:13,208 --> 00:26:15,250
She seems like someone
straight out of a TV drama.

313
00:26:16,500 --> 00:26:17,708
That's what you call an idol.

314
00:26:18,208 --> 00:26:20,375
You guys haven't seen
someone truly impressive.

315
00:26:20,625 --> 00:26:22,851
There's someone at our school
even more eye-catching than Lin Xia.

316
00:26:22,875 --> 00:26:23,458
See?

317
00:26:23,875 --> 00:26:25,666
That guy Zhan Wang from my brother's class.

318
00:26:25,875 --> 00:26:26,583
He's handsome,

319
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:28,000
a great fighter,

320
00:26:28,291 --> 00:26:29,500
and amazing at sports.

321
00:26:30,041 --> 00:26:30,625
Plus,

322
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:33,500
he's from a truly wealthy family.

323
00:26:33,750 --> 00:26:35,166
Now that's a real star.

324
00:26:35,708 --> 00:26:37,041
Senior Zhan Wang.

325
00:26:37,250 --> 00:26:38,708
He does seem pretty famous.

326
00:26:39,291 --> 00:26:39,708
Yeah, yeah.

327
00:26:39,833 --> 00:26:40,833
The Jinx's friend.

328
00:26:40,958 --> 00:26:43,158
Those two are practically
joined at the hip these days.

329
00:26:43,375 --> 00:26:45,041
That might not be the case for long.

330
00:26:45,166 --> 00:26:45,916
I heard...

331
00:26:46,125 --> 00:26:47,892
the 'fairy' and senior Zhan
Wang know each other.

332
00:26:47,916 --> 00:26:48,916
Someone saw them earlier,

333
00:26:49,083 --> 00:26:50,559
coming out of the
teachers' office together.

334
00:26:50,583 --> 00:26:51,851
So what if they know each other?

335
00:26:51,875 --> 00:26:54,500
My brother and Brother
Zhan Wang hang out every day.

336
00:26:54,666 --> 00:26:55,666
They're the real deal.

337
00:26:56,291 --> 00:26:58,375
Anyway, I have to bring
them their lunch later.

338
00:26:59,000 --> 00:26:59,666
Then,

339
00:26:59,958 --> 00:27:01,518
I'll get a look at that 'fairy' myself.

340
00:27:01,666 --> 00:27:02,986
And see if she's really all that.

341
00:27:03,791 --> 00:27:04,458
Xu Nuo.

342
00:27:04,708 --> 00:27:06,958
Are you scouting the
enemy for your brother?

343
00:27:07,208 --> 00:27:09,488
Or are you checking her out
for your 'Brother Zhan Wang'?

344
00:27:10,291 --> 00:27:11,291
None of your business.

345
00:27:12,041 --> 00:27:13,201
I'm just bringing them lunch.

346
00:27:15,416 --> 00:27:16,208
Hope you don't get the cold shoulder.

347
00:27:16,208 --> 00:27:17,208
Look, she's mad now.

348
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,000
You.

349
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,666
Your hair, on this side...

350
00:27:27,833 --> 00:27:29,083
Bro! Brother Zhan Wang!

351
00:27:29,500 --> 00:27:30,500
Time to eat.

352
00:27:35,750 --> 00:27:37,541
You must be the new girl.

353
00:27:38,500 --> 00:27:39,500
You're so pretty.

354
00:27:40,750 --> 00:27:41,870
I'm Xu Yuan's little sister,

355
00:27:42,041 --> 00:27:43,041
Xu Nuo.

356
00:27:47,416 --> 00:27:48,416
So you're Xu Nuo.

357
00:27:50,291 --> 00:27:51,291
You're so cute.

358
00:27:55,833 --> 00:27:56,250
Bro.

359
00:27:56,791 --> 00:27:57,791
Brother Zhan Wang.

360
00:27:57,958 --> 00:27:59,124
My brother specifically asked Mom

361
00:27:59,125 --> 00:28:00,833
to make your favorite pork ribs.

362
00:28:01,166 --> 00:28:02,375
You two are really close.

363
00:28:02,916 --> 00:28:04,836
My brother remembers
everything you like to eat.

364
00:28:11,291 --> 00:28:12,291
However,

365
00:28:12,791 --> 00:28:15,000
I don't think Zhan Wang
has ever eaten cilantro.

366
00:28:16,291 --> 00:28:17,625
He can't stand even a hint of it.

367
00:28:17,791 --> 00:28:20,208
And it looks like this dish
is full of chopped cilantro.

368
00:28:27,958 --> 00:28:29,278
I'll remember that for next time.

369
00:28:34,333 --> 00:28:37,000
So picky and so proud of it.

